# Mobile App Patterns

## Routing

Use Expo Router (file-based). Tabs live in `app/(tabs)/`. Kitchen Mode is a full-screen modal at `app/kitchen-mode.tsx`.

## State Management

Use Zustand stores in `stores/`. Four stores:
- `dateStore` — Selected date, shared across Dashboard/Log/Kitchen Mode. Defaults to today on app launch. All entry creation and queries use this date.
- `draftStore` — Kitchen Mode draft cards and session state
- `dailyLogStore` — Dashboard entries, frequent/recent foods (filtered by selected date)
- `goalStore` — Daily macro targets

## Components

- Bottom sheets use a consistent full-height pattern (FoodDetailSheet, CreateFoodSheet) or lightweight pattern (EditEntrySheet).
- Draft cards in Kitchen Mode have three visual states: normal, clarifying (highlight/pulse), creating (fields fill in progressively).
- Every food entry row shows a source indicator icon (database or custom).

## Styling

Minimal, clean, Apple Health aesthetic. Generous white space. Define all colors, typography, and spacing in `constants/theme.ts` — never use inline magic values.

## Services

- `api.ts` — REST client wrapping fetch, typed request/response
- `voiceSession.ts` — WebSocket client for Kitchen Mode
- `speech.ts` — On-device STT via `expo-speech-recognition`, TTS via Expo Speech
